          "date": "2026-04-22 02:03:48.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-20178 utils: lfs setstripe compression support",
        "message": "LU-20178 utils: lfs setstripe compression support\n\nAdd compression options to the lfs setstripe command for\ncreating files with client-side compression:\n\n- lfs.c: add --compress-type/-Z and --compress-chunk\n  options to lfs setstripe, with validation that\n  compression requires a composite layout (-E flag).\n  Supported types: lz4, lz4hc, lzo, none.\n  Supported chunk sizes: 64k, 128k, 256k, 512k,\n  1m, 2m, 4m.\n- liblustreapi.c: pass compression parameters through\n  the layout API to the kernel\n- liblustreapi_layout.c: implement getter/setter\n  functions for compression type and chunk size in\n  llapi_layout component entries\n- lustreapi.h: declare new layout compression API\n  functions\n\nUsage example:\n  lfs setstripe -E eof -Z lz4 --compress-chunk 256k file\n\nSigned-off-by: Brian Barbisch <brbarbis@microsoft.com>\nTest-Parameters: Ignore\nChange-Id: I25dd819d923e19d846bf86c94306be03730b5f13\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
